"It is noteworthy that with the current slow growth in peak demand, the shifting of project Commercial Operations Dates (CODs) will not address the imminent oversupply challenges. Clearly, a different model is required that will deliver revenues for these projects and at the same time reduce retail tariffs as per Government policy," read the April 2020 letter sent to the ministry. 



