"One option is to create a separate entity dedicated to entering into PPAs with generators on behalf of the Government." 

On the spot 

Just before his first term ended in July, the regulator was on the spot after it emerged there had been an error in the fuel pump price calculation, leading to a huge jump in prices in August. 

The energy regulator had failed to correctly compute the prices for the June/July period, an error whose correction in the July/August fuel price caused a massive hike in pump prices. 

At the board, opinion was split regarding Mr Oimeke's performance, with his August suspension testing the unity of the 11-member team led by the retired Supreme Court judge. 

In fact, a board member even swore an affidavit in Mr Oimeke’s defence in court. Engineer Samuel Maugo told the judge that Oimeke had been rightfully appointed and confirmed by Energy Cabinet Secretary Charles Keter in May 2020, long before the petition came up. 

The Monday board meetings are said to have been stormy and the discussions ended with the replacement of Mr Oimeke by his former intern at Epra, Mr Daniel Kiptoo, who had risen to be Petroleum Legal Advisor to the Cabinet Secretary. 

For the second time in less than three months, a new person was being appointed to act in Oimeke's absence. 



